servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Trim and peel @carrot{3%ounce}; grate on the largest holes of a #box grater{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together grated carrot, @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, half the cilantro, @sugar{1%tsp}, and a @salt{pinch} until thoroughly combined.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 tsp sugar.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp} and cook until chicken is coated and glaze has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} with @sriracha{1%tsp} to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{} and fill with chicken and slaw (draining first). Top with sriracha mayo, @crispy fried onions{1}, and remaining cilantro. Serve.